{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781683009,"nonce":"UJ3pM/wXdaMCfBgTHN/noW7b7rg=","title":"Subqueries, CTEs (WITH), and set operations (UNION/INTERSECT/EXCEPT)","message":"No compositional query support beyond a single flat SELECT:\n\n- Subqueries: scalar subqueries in projections/predicates, IN (subquery), and EXISTS (subquery) / NOT EXISTS.\n- CTEs: WITH name AS (...) including the ability to select from a CTE as a source. (Recursive CTEs can be a follow-up.)\n- Set operations: UNION / UNION ALL / INTERSECT / EXCEPT between two compatible selects.\n\nThis is the largest structural gap after aggregation. It pushes on the type-level AST in `crates/squealy/src/query.rs` / expr.rs because a subquery is a query used as an expression or source, so SelectQuery needs to be usable in operand and source position. Worth designing the source/expression abstraction with this in mind even if delivered incrementally (EXISTS and IN-subquery first, CTEs and set ops after).","files":null}]}